Huge Data:
Data is growing at a rapid pace these days and needs to be managed dynamically with access to it everywhere.
Big data technoloies like Hadoop and spark provides the platform to handle huge data on distributed servers.
It also allows users to process the raw data coming in without any predefined format.

Speed,Capacity and Scalability of cloud:

Scalability is major drawback of large network of computers. For higher rates of data, the framework must be 
capable of handling those in quick time.
Storage is managed on distributed system by big data technology.

End users can have data in required form:

Big data technologies provide data visualization tools such as easy-to-read charts,graphs and slideshows.
